acceptedAnswer.text: The subscription terms of use can be found here. (https://www.walmart.com/help/article/walmart-subscriptions-terms-of-use/f05e20e6c2544640a88cfa2aa4947aac)

mainEntity.name: How can I start using subscriptions?

acceptedAnswer.text: Subscriptions are available on thousands of everyday favorites such as groceries, pet supplies, pantry staples, home cleaning and more. If the item is eligible, you will be able to select “Subscribe” & choose how often you want your item. To participate, you must have a valid Walmart account, shipping address & payment method on file. Sign into your account or create a new account to get started.

There is no charge to subscribe to items. Shipping is free on orders over $35. Certain items eligible for subscriptions may require a scheduled delivery. Delivery fees apply to all scheduled deliveries.  A minimum order fee of $6.99 applies to all orders below $35, and bag fees may apply to delivery orders in certain locations.

mainEntity.name: Will I pay shipping or delivery fees if I’m a Walmart+ member?

acceptedAnswer.text: Walmart+ members can start using subscriptions at no added cost to membership and get free shipping and delivery on all orders. Any delivery order under $35 will still be subject to the minimum order fee.

mainEntity.name: How do I skip my subscriptions?

acceptedAnswer.text: You can easily manage your subscriptions in the app or online. Log in to your account & select My Subscriptions under Subscription & Plans section. Select the subscription you wish to skip. Select “Skip” on each item you would like to skip.

mainEntity.name: How do I cancel my subscriptions?

acceptedAnswer.text: You can easily manage your subscriptions in the app or online. Log in to your account, click account & select My Subscriptions. Click on the subscription you wish to cancel. Select “Unsubscribe”.

mainEntity.name: How do I change the frequency on my subscriptions?

acceptedAnswer.text:
You can easily manage your subscriptions in the app or online. Log in to your account and select My Subscriptions. Click on the subscription you wish to change. Select “Edit” next to frequency. Update the frequency to your requested change.

mainEntity.name: How do I change my delivery timing?

acceptedAnswer.text: You can easily manage your subscriptions in the app or online. Log in to your account & select My Subscriptions. Select “Edit” on the right of the screen. Choose your new delivery day and/or time.

mainEntity.name: Why did the price of my subscription item change?

acceptedAnswer.text: We aim to deliver low prices and don’t expect them to change often. We’ll let you know the price you’ll be charged prior to each fulfillment.

mainEntity.name: Can I subscribe to all items on Walmart.com?

acceptedAnswer.text: No, not all items are available for subscription service. Please see the individual item page for details.

mainEntity.name: How do I return a subscription order?

acceptedAnswer.text: Subscription orders follow normal return processes.

mainEntity.name: How do I amend a subscription delivery order?

acceptedAnswer.text: While your order is still preparing, you can add or remove items, increase or decrease quantities, and allow or disallow substitutions. To edit items in an order, select Account, select Purchase History, and select Edit Items.

data.description: Wisairt's ultimate 36V electric ride on dirt bike for kids 5-10 years old! This high-speed electric dirt bicycle rockets to 15.5 MPH with its powerful 250W motor (315W peak) while offering controlled safety through 3-speed modes (5/7.5/15.5 MPH). Built for outdoor riding, our dirt bike features a long-range 36V 5.2Ah battery (riding range up to 10 miles/2 hours), all-terrain 12" rubber tires, and a rugged 133 LBS capacity frame. Safety shines with instant-stop drum brakes + power-off tech and shock-absorbing suspension for bumpy terrain, while the waterproof seat and kid-optimized 21.2" saddle height (fits 40-60" young riders) make this electric motorcycle for kids the perfect durable, easy-ride kids' ride on dirt bike– the ultimate electric ride on motorcycle for young adventurers!

review.name: Perfect gift
review.reviewBody: The Wisairt 36V Kids Electric Dirt Bike is super easy to set up.  It took maybe 30 minutes solo.  All you need is a hex and Phillip's screwdriver.  They do supply these inside the box.  The battery lasts more than an hour on continuous riding, but it is advertised for 12.  The speed is more than fast enough and it has the twist grips for speed control.  The kids pick up pretty quickly on how to use it.  Overall, a very nice and sturdy ride for the kids.  Perfect gift.

review.name: Super cool !
review.reviewBody: This is a powerful and super cool electric off-road vehicle. Every child should love it. The quality is excellent, and installation is very simple, taking only about 20 minutes. It has three speed settings, allowing you to adjust the speed according to different age groups.

review.name: Good！！！
review.reviewBody:
I bought this electric dirt bike as a gift for my nephew, and it turned out to be a huge hit. He was beyond excited when he saw it—it looks super cool in person, just like a real motocross bike but perfectly sized for kids. The blue color is vibrant and really stands out, and the design overall feels very solid and well-made.

The speed is just right—fast enough to feel thrilling but still safe for a young rider. It handles well on grass, pavement, and even slightly uneven terrain, and the suspension does a good job smoothing out the ride. The battery life has been great so far; he's been able to ride for a couple of hours on a single charge, which keeps him happy and active.

Assembly was straightforward, and it didn't take long at all. It's also not too heavy, which makes it easier to move around and store when not in use.

Honestly, it's one of the best gifts I've gotten for him. He's constantly asking to ride it and even started wearing his little helmet and gloves like a real biker. If you're looking for something fun, exciting, and actually well-built for kids, this bike is totally worth it. Highly recommend!

review.name: Perfect E-Bike for Young Riders!
review.reviewBody: We got this Wisairt 36V electric dirt bike for kid, and it's been an absolute hit! The speed is just right — exciting but safe — and the twist grip throttle makes it feel like a real motorcycle. It holds a good charge and the 10-mile range is perfect for a day at the park or riding around the neighborhood. The waterproof seat is a nice touch for unexpected weather. It's sturdy, easy to handle, and has given our kid so much confidence outdoors. Highly recommended for any young rider ready for their first dirt bike adventure!

review.name: Best purchase ever
review.reviewBody: My daughter has been riding this since it came in. I actually want one for myself! It goes really fast but it also has 2 speeds. This is the best riding toy I've ever purchased. Came already assembled and charged. I did have to attach the steering wheel and battery but it was very simple. I would recommend this to anyone who has a child that likes to go fast and have fun. It's very durable and made well. All positive and no negatives about this product so far!!
This was a great quality purchase for my 8 year old boy. The speed is as advertised. I have a 2 yo who loves to ride with his older brother as well. I definitely recommend this product.

review.name: LOADS OF FUN
review.reviewBody: This thing is a hoot!  If you are 180 lbs or less, give it a go. My granddaughters love it.  ONLY WORKS ON A FLAT BLACKTOP OR TENNIS COURT-TYPE surface.  No off-roading with this thing

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody: The quality of it is really nice. The product is usable for both adults and children, really fun. There are two speeds, high speed is great for adults and slower speed is better for children. It is worth its price.

review.name: Very nice bike for the money
review.reviewBody: Son absolutely loves it..he turned 8 and is avg size and the bike size is perfect for him.

review.name: Disappointed
review.reviewBody: So excited to give this to my Grandson. We had to fix the brakes after using it 2 times. Took it to a guy who works on bikes. He fixed it and they keep failing. Today they went completely out. Very disappointed!!!
